耳垂是[[耳廓|耳廓]]的基本结构之一，属于体外可见的部分，而耳廓与[[外耳道|外耳道]]共同组成了[[耳|耳]]结构中的[[外耳|外耳]]。<ref>{{Cite web|title=External Ear - an overview|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/medicine-and-dentistry/external-ear|accessdate=2021-03-07|work=|publisher=Science Direct|language=en|archive-date=2021-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315145541/https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/medicine-and-dentistry/external-ear|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|chapter=Anatomy, Head and Neck, Ear|title=StatPearls|url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK470359/|publisher=StatPearls Publishing|date=2021|location=Treasure Island (FL)|pmid=29262017|first=Alice|last=Szymanski|first2=Zachary|last2=Geiger|access-date=2021-03-07|archive-date=2021-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315145619/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK470359/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

耳垂由[[上皮组织|上皮组织]]和[[结缔组织|结缔组织]]构成，内部包含许多[[神经末梢|神经末梢]]，故对一些人而言耳垂属于[[性敏感部位|性敏感部位]]。<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|title=7 Feel-Good Moves to Try Tonight|url=https://www.webmd.com/sex-relationships/features/7-awesome-erogenous-zones|accessdate=2021-03-07|work=WebMD|language=en|archive-date=2021-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315145629/https://www.webmd.com/sex-relationships/features/7-awesome-erogenous-zones|dead-url=no}}</ref>

多数人的耳垂是自由下垂型，而另一些人的耳垂下部与侧脸相连。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Genetics of Earlobes|url=https://www.news-medical.net/health/Genetics-of-Earlobes.aspx|accessdate=2021-03-07|date=2017-07-04|last=|first=|work=|publisher=News-Medical.net|language=en|archive-date=2021-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315145609/https://www.news-medical.net/health/Genetics-of-Earlobes.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 功能 ==
耳垂内不含[[软骨|软骨]]，且内部有较多[[血液|血液]]供应，故可保持耳部温度以及平衡。<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Anatomy of the Earlobe|url=https://www.verywellhealth.com/earlobe-anatomy-5092216|accessdate=2021-03-07|work=Verywell Health|language=en|archive-date=2021-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315145559/https://www.verywellhealth.com/earlobe-anatomy-5092216|dead-url=no}}</ref> 但一般认为，耳垂并不具有重要的生物学功能。<ref name=":1" />

== 临床 ==
正常情况下，耳垂结构平滑，但某些情况下会出现[[耳垂摺痕|耳垂折痕]]。<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|title=Ear lobe crease: MedlinePlus Medical Encyclopedia Image|url=https://medlineplus.gov/ency/imagepages/9287.htm|accessdate=2021-03-07|work=medlineplus.gov|language=en|archive-date=2021-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210321154401/https://medlineplus.gov/ency/imagepages/9287.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref> 譬如，儿童的耳垂折痕有时与遗传紊乱有关，如[[貝克威思－威德曼症候群|贝克威思－威德曼症候群]]。<ref name=":2" />

此外，一些早期研究认为[[耳垂摺痕|耳垂折痕]]可能与[[心脏病|心脏病]]和[[冠心病|冠心病]]的高风险有关。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=A New Wrinkle to the Earlobe Crease|url=https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jamainternalmedicine/fullarticle/607639|last=Brady|first=Priscilla M.|last2=Zive|first2=Marc A.|date=1987-01-01|journal=Archives of Internal Medicine|issue=1|doi=10.1001/archinte.1987.00370010069017|volume=147|pages=65–66|language=en|issn=0003-9926|last3=Goldberg|first3=Robert J.|last4=Gore|first4=Joel M.|last5=Dalen|first5=James E.}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite web|title=Diagonal earlobe crease (Frank's sign)|url=https://stanfordmedicine25.stanford.edu/blog/archive/2015/what-is-the-name-of-this-sign.html|accessdate=2021-03-07|work=Stanford Medicine 25|language=en|archive-date=2021-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315145633/https://stanfordmedicine25.stanford.edu/blog/archive/2015/what-is-the-name-of-this-sign.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{Cite journal|title=Ear lobe crease: a marker of coronary artery disease?|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4697048/|last=Agouridis|first=Aris P.|last2=Elisaf|first2=Moses S.|date=2015-12-10|journal=Archives of Medical Science : AMS|issue=6|doi=10.5114/aoms.2015.56340|volume=11|pages=1145–1155|issn=1734-1922|pmc=4697048|pmid=26788075|last3=Nair|first3=Devaki R.|last4=Mikhailidis|first4=Dimitri P.|access-date=2021-03-07|archive-date=2021-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315145657/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4697048/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":5">{{Cite journal|title=Earlobe crease (Frank’s sign) and coronary heart disease|url=https://academic.oup.com/qjmed/article/113/12/902/5820018|last=Chauhdary|first=W. A.|last2=Rubel|first2=A. R.|date=2020-12-01|journal=QJM: An International Journal of Medicine|issue=12|doi=10.1093/qjmed/hcaa129|volume=113|pages=902–902|language=en|issn=1460-2725|last3=Bashir|first3=A.|last4=Hla Aye|first4=M. T.|last5=Javed|first5=N.|last6=Soe|first6=Z. N.|last7=Sharif|first7=S. M. A.|last8=Mani|first8=B. I.|last9=Oomen|first9=M.|access-date=2021-03-07|archive-date=2021-03-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210328010939/https://academic.oup.com/qjmed/article/113/12/902/5820018|dead-url=no}}</ref> 但此后也有研究认为，随着年龄的增长，耳垂可能会自然出现折痕，而与此同时年龄大的人群患心脑血管疾病的概率本身也比年轻人高，所以二者并不直接相关。<ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4" /><ref name=":5" />

